-The remaining posture regularization in \SRB{} is only
+The reduced model now uses the following extra posture regularizers:
+\begin{align}
+r_{\mathrm{torso\_rot\_dev}}
+&=
+\sum_{j \in \mathcal{J}_{torso\_rot}}
+|q_j-q^{default}_j|,\\
+r_{\mathrm{torso\_trans\_dev}}
+&=
+\sum_{j \in \mathcal{J}_{torso\_trans}}
+|q_j-q^{default}_j|,
+\end{align}
+where
+\begin{equation}
+\mathcal{J}_{torso\_rot} = \{roll, pitch, yaw\},
+\qquad
+\mathcal{J}_{torso\_trans} = \{t_x, t_y, t_z\}.
+\end{equation}
+The leg regularizer remains
 \begin{equation}
 r_{\mathrm{leg\_dev}}
 =
 \sum_{j \in \mathcal{J}_{hip\_roll,hip\_yaw}}
-|q_j-q^{default}_j|,
+|q_j-q^{default}_j|.
 \end{equation}
-which is exactly the leg-deviation term already present in \UT{}.
 
